Experimenting with the following program running in the background:

```rust
use copypasta::ClipboardProvider;
use copypasta::ClipboardContext;

fn main() {
    let mut ctx = ClipboardContext::new().unwrap();

    loop {
        println!("{:?}", ctx.get_contents());

        std::thread::sleep(std::time::Duration::from_millis(100));
    }
}
```

After a few hours of uptime, I don't see a lag yet, but I do see occasional errors:

```
Ok("Maybe there\'s something with")
Ok("Maybe there\'s something with")
Err(UnexpectedType(0))
Ok("Maybe there\'s something with")
Ok("Maybe there\'s something with")
Err(UnexpectedType(0))
